                        <div class="row">
                            <h4>There are two ways to define a schedule:</h4>
                            <div class="col-md-12">
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/GeneralSchedule.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail" style="float: left; margin-right: 16px;">

                                <h4 id="line3_1">1. General schedule</h4>
                                <p><b>Settings -> General schedule</b></p>
                                <p>Here the schedule is set and is general which means if you set the schedule for Saturday it applies to the next weeks Saturday and the one after that and so on.</p>
                                <p>As shown in the figure below, to add your clinic schedule, you have to choose in the Day, Shift, From time, To time, Service and maximum capacity.</p>
                                <p>The "Day" drop down list is to select the days you want to define schedule for.</p>
                                <p>In general, there are two types of shifts in which you can define in the system, Morning shift which starts from 06:00 - 14:00, and Evening shift which starts from 14:00 - 23:00 </p>
                                <p>"Service" is the services you offer for the patients to take appointments from, you can drop down the "Services" list and choose a preffered timing for the services.</p>
                                <p>"Maximum capacity" field is to define how many patients can reserve an appointment during the shifts you defined.</p>
                            </div>
                            <!-- end col -->

                        </div>
                        <!-- end row -->

                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-12" style="margin-top: 16px; ">

                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/AddShift.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <hr>


                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-12">
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/Doctor_Button.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail" style="float: left; margin-right: 16px;">

                                <h4 id="line3_2">2. Manual Scheduling</h4>
                                <p><b>Doctors -> Scheduling</b></p>
                                <p>Here is the day by day scheduling. You can put a separate schedule here for example for Saturday and it will apply to this Saturday only not every week.</p>
                                <p>To add a specific schedule for the for a day in the week use this type of scheduling.</p>
                            </div>
                            <!-- end col -->

                        </div>
                        <!-- end row -->

                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-12" style="margin-top: 16px; ">
                                <p>First hit "Scheduling" button the the scheduling table will open.</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/scheduling.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <p>In the below scheduling table, choose the preffered day to put a specific schedule for by using <img src="~/images/guide/upload/NextBack_button.jpg" style="width: 80px; vertical-align: baseline;"> or select <img src="~/images/guide/upload/TodayCOA.jpg" style="width: 55px; vertical-align: baseline;"> if you want to schedule a specific schedule for it.  </p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/manual_scheduling.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <p>Drag and drop the timing you want to set for the day you have selected and a new window will pop up as shown below, fill in the required fields then hit on "Save"</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/ManualSchedulingConfiguration.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <p>Finally as seen in the below image, the schedule for that specific day will be set.</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/manual_scheduling2.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <hr>
                                <p>To disable the doctor for a period due to non-availability do as follows: <b>first </b>click on the timing you want as shown below</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/DisableSchedule.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <p><b>Second</b> when the below window pops open change the status from <img src="~/images/guide/upload/StatusON.jpg" style="width: 30px; vertical-align: baseline;"> to <img src="~/images/guide/upload/StatusOff.jpg" style="width: 30px; vertical-align: baseline;"> the hit the <img src="~/images/guide/upload/Update_Button.jpg" style="width: 50px; vertical-align: baseline;"> button</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/EditScheduleWindow1.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <hr>
                                <p>To disable the doctor for a a whole day: <b>first </b>click on the timing you want as shown below</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/DisableDoctorForAllDay.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <p><b>Second</b> when the below window pops open, you have all of the information of the doctor disabling, then hit "disable doctor for all day"</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/DisableDoctorWindow.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">
                                <p>Then when disabled the below window will be shown.</p>
                                <img src="~/images/guide/upload/DoctorDisableForAllDay.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive img-thumbnail">






                            </div>
